****************************************************************** Np-236m Evaluation T. Kawano, P. Talou Jan. 2012 ****************************************************************** Evaluation based on: ENDF/B-VII.1 (JENDL-4.0) Np236 ground state data CoH3 calculation to the ground and 60keV levels
The coupled-channels calculation in JENDL-4.0 assumes the following level scheme, where all the excited levels except for 60keV meta state are postulated.
------------------- No. Ex(MeV) J PI ------------------- 0 0.00000 6 - * 1 0.05600 7 - * 2 0.06000 1 + 3 0.07600 2 + 4 0.10000 3 + 5 0.12000 8 - * 6 0.13200 4 +
First we followed the same g.s. calculation as JENDL to try to reproduce all the g.s. cross sections. Then the same parameters are employed to calculate cross sections on the excited state, with the coupling of 1+, 2+, 3+, and 4+ states.
MF1 MT452, 455, 456 same as ground state
MF2 the same resonance parameters for the ground state, but spins were changed.
MF3 The following cross sections were evaluated by applying a scaling factor of F to the ground state cross sections, where F = CoH(meta) / CoH(ground).
MT 16 (n,2n) MT 17 (n,3n) MT 18 fission MT 37 (n,4n)
These sections below were replaced by the CoH excited state calculations.
MT 1 total MT 2 elastic = total - sum of partials MT 51 - 56 discrete level inelastic scattering MT 91 continuum inelastic scattering MT 102 radiative capture
MF4 MT 2, 51 - 56, new CoH calculations
MF5 same as g.s.
MF6 MT 51 - 56 the angular distributions for the disrete levels removed, and given in new evaluations in MF4
MT 16, 17, 37, 91, 102 same as g.s.
MF12 MT18 same as g.s.
MF14 MT18 same as g.s.
MF15 MT18 same as g.s.
